---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Behaviour Expectations | ISJ Jakarta"
  description="ISJ's expectations for pupil conduct and parent partnership. Covers respect, inclusion, uniform, attendance, and communication."
  canonicalUrl="/admissions/behaviour-expectations"
>

  <section class="pt-32 lg:pt-40 pb-20 lg:pb-28 px-6">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[640px]">

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="mb-14">
        <p class="text-[12px] font-semibold tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-charcoal-muted mb-4" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">Admissions</p>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-[length:var(--text-2xl)] font-light text-navy leading-[1.1] mb-6">Behaviour Expectations</h1>
        <p class="text-[15px] text-charcoal-muted leading-relaxed" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          A positive school community depends on shared values and mutual respect. These expectations apply to all pupils and to the families who partner with ISJ in their child's education. For the full policy framework, see the <a href="/policies/behaviour" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">Behaviour Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Pupils -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-navy mb-8" style="font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);">For Pupils</h2>

        <div class="space-y-0" style="font-size: 15px; font-family: var(--font-body); color: var(--color-charcoal); line-height: 1.75;">
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Be gentle, kind, and fair in all interactions.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Use respectful words. How something is said matters as much as what is said.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Include others. Look out for anyone who is alone or left out.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Listen carefully when others are speaking.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Tell the truth. Honesty builds trust.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Share resources and space considerately.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Work hard and take pride in the effort put into all tasks.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Take care of personal belongings and school property.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Bullying of any kind is not tolerated. This includes online behaviour.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Digital citizenship applies in and out of school. Technology is used responsibly and respectfully.</div>
          <div class="py-3">When mistakes happen, ISJ uses a restorative approach: pupils are supported to understand the impact of their actions and to make things right.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Parents / Guardians -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-navy mb-8" style="font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);">For Parents and Guardians</h2>

        <div class="space-y-0" style="font-size: 15px; font-family: var(--font-body); color: var(--color-charcoal); line-height: 1.75;">
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Reinforce ISJ's values at home. Children develop best when school and home are consistent.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Communicate with staff respectfully at all times, in person and in writing.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Ensure regular attendance and punctuality. Notify the school in advance of any planned absence.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Send pupils in correct uniform each day. Hair should be tidy; jewellery, makeup, and nail polish are not permitted.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Label all belongings clearly.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Collect pupils promptly at the end of the school day. Notify the school if someone other than the usual contact will be collecting.</div>
          <div class="py-3 border-b border-navy/[0.05]">Raise concerns directly with the school rather than through parent group chats. Group chats are not an appropriate channel for school matters.</div>
          <div class="py-3">Treat all members of the school community with courtesy. Staff, pupils, and other families all deserve a respectful environment.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Back link -->
      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-navy/[0.06]">
        <a href="/admissions/how-to-apply" class="text-[13px] text-charcoal-muted hover:text-navy transition-colors" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          &larr; Back to Admissions
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
